\begin{align*}
&(1001001)(1010101)+(989899)(1001001)\\
&\qquad -(1001)(989899)-(1010101)(1001) 
\end{align*}

We can see that (1001001) appears in the first two terms, and (1001) and (1010101) appear in the last two terms. This suggests we can group them:

\begin{align*}
&(1001001)(1010101 + 989899) - (1001)(989899 + 1010101) 
\end{align*}

Now, notice that (1010101 + 989899) = 2000000.  Substituting this in, we get:

\begin{align*}
&(1001001)(2000000) - (1001)(2000000) 
\end{align*}

We can factor out 2000000:

\begin{align*}
&2000000(1001001 - 1001) \\
&= 2000000(1000000)
\end{align*}

Finally, this simplifies to:

$$2 \times 10^{12}$$

So the rightmost non-zero digit is 2, and it's followed by 12 zeroes.

The answer is $\boxed{(2,12)}$.

